(29, 27, 'a:45:{s:10:"subtitle_1";s:9:"Policy no";s:5:"des_1";s:14:"<p>ECP-228</p>";s:5:"pos_1";s:1:"1";s:10:"subtitle_2";s:7:"Version";s:5:"des_2";s:11:"<p>13.0</p>";s:5:"pos_2";s:1:"2";s:10:"subtitle_3";s:11:"Approved By";s:5:"des_3";s:17:"<p>Prem Anand</p>";s:5:"pos_3";s:1:"3";s:10:"subtitle_4";s:14:"Effective Date";s:5:"des_4";s:23:"<p>January 15, 2014</p>";s:5:"pos_4";s:1:"4";s:10:"subtitle_5";s:7:"Purpose";s:5:"des_5";s:140:"<p>Obtain satisfactory assurances with impacted regulations that the Business Associate will appropriately safeguard all corporate data.</p>";s:5:"pos_5";s:1:"5";s:10:"subtitle_6";s:5:"Scope";s:5:"des_6";s:423:"<p>This policy applies to PIPL in its entirety, including all employees, workforce members, physicians and affiliates. &nbsp;In addition, some third parties such as contractors or vendors may be required to abide by parts of this policy if required by PIPL in a Business Associate Contract (BAC). &nbsp;Further, the policy applies to the network, systems and applications that process, store or transmit corporate data.</p>";s:5:"pos_6";s:1:"6";s:10:"subtitle_7";s:6:"Policy";s:5:"des_7";s:2032:"<p>PIPL will identify all organizations that process corporate data.&nbsp; Such businesses will include all existing BAC(s) executed by PIPL.</p><p>PIPL will review the flow of corporate data to all outside entities and identify how such information is transmitted, and the requirements for secure and compliant processing of corporate data at the Business Associate site.</p><p>PIPL will review all existing BAC(s) and ensure that all such agreements are modified with addendums or revised for compliance with impacted regulations.</p><p>Business Associates are required to report any instance of misuse or unauthorized disclosure of PIPL&rsquo;s corporate data.</p><p>The termination of a BAC with the Business Associate must result in the return or destruction of PIPL&rsquo;s corporate data.</p><p>Business Associates must train all members of their workforce that process or come into contact with PIPL&rsquo;s corporate data.&nbsp; This training must include awareness of the requirements of the appropriate regulations as well as information about the Business Associate&rsquo;s security policies and procedures.</p><p>PIPL must have the right to audit the Business Associate in the event of violations related to PIPL&rsquo;s corporate data.</p><p>PIPL must reserve the right to take &ldquo;reasonable steps&rdquo; including canceling the BAC without penalty.</p><p>If the Business Associate intends to process or transmit PIPL&rsquo;s corporate data outside the United States of America, then PIPL must be informed of specific details related to such processing or transmission and reserves the right to not authorize any such flow of corporate data.</p><p>BAC(s) will be maintained by the Compliance Department in an electronic or printed form, and will be updated immediately as a Business Associate is added or removed, or otherwise changes name or status.&nbsp; PIPL will review all existing BAC(s) and ensure that all such agreements are modified with Addendums or revised for compliance with impacted regulations.</p>";s:5:"pos_7";s:1:"7";s:10:"subtitle_8";s:9:"Retention";s:5:"des_8";s:342:"<p>Every policy and procedure revision/replacement will be maintained for a minimum of six years from the date of its creation or when it was last in effect, whichever is later. Other PIPL requirements may stipulate a longer retention.</p><p>Log-in audit information and logs relevant to security incidents must be retained for six years.</p>";s:5:"pos_8";s:1:"8";s:10:"subtitle_9";s:10:"Compliance";s:5:"des_9";s:276:"<p>Failure to comply with this or any other security policy will result in disciplinary actions as per the Sanction Policy.</p><p>Legal actions also may be taken for violations of applicable regulations and standards such as HIPAA, GLB, Sarbanes-Oxley, PCI DSS and others.</p>";s:5:"pos_9";s:1:"9";s:11:"subtitle_10";s:7:"Form(s)";s:6:"des_10";s:11:"<p>None</p>";s:6:"pos_10";s:2:"10";s:11:"subtitle_11";s:10:"References";s:6:"des_11";s:1854:"<ul><li>Omnibus HIPAA Final Rulemaking, <a href="http://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/administrative/omnibus/index.html">http://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/administrative/omnibus/index.html</a></li><li>International Standards Organization (ISO 27002).</li><li>HIPAA Final Security Rule, 45 CFR Parts 160, 162, and 164, Department of Health and Human Services, <a href="http://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/administrative/securityrule/">http://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/administrative/securityrule/</a> February 20, 2003.</li><li>American Reinvestment and Recovery Act of 2009 (ARRA)/(HITECH). <a href="http://frwebgate.access.gpo.gov/cgi-bin/getdoc.cgi?dbname=111_cong_bills&amp;docid=f:h1enr.pdf">http://frwebgate.access.gpo.gov/cgi-bin/getdoc.cgi?dbname=111_cong_bills&amp;docid=f:h1enr.pdf.</a></li><li>(The HITECH&nbsp;Act begins at&nbsp;H.R. 1-112 through 1-165 (pp. 112 through 165 in the document).&nbsp;The security and privacy provisions are found at Subtitle D &shy; Privacy, beginning H.R. 1-144 (p. 144)).</li><li>Health Information Privacy, Security, and Your EHR</li><li><a href="http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/ehr-privacy-security">http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/ehr-privacy-security</a></li><li>Achieve Meaningful Use: Protect Electronic Health Information</li><li><a href="http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/achieve-meaningful-use/core-measures/protect-electronic-health-information">http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/achieve-meaningful-use/core-measures/protect-electronic-health-information</a> <a href="http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/achieve-meaningful-use/core-measures-2/protect-electronic-health-information">http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/achieve-meaningful-use/core-measures-2/protect-electronic-health-information</a></li></ul>";s:6:"pos_11";s:2:"11";s:11:"subtitle_12";s:7:"Contact";s:6:"des_12";s:207:"<p>Maria Vasanth Prem Anand, Information Security Officer<br />6, Manakula Vinayagar St<br />Kailash Nagar, ECR. Lawspet, Puducherry 605008<br />India<br />E: prem.anand@pabrai.com<br />P: 1.800.425.9030</p>";s:6:"pos_12";s:2:"12";s:11:"subtitle_13";s:14:"Policy History";s:6:"des_13";s:47:"<p>Initial effective date: January 15, 2014</p>";s:6:"pos_13";s:2:"13";s:11:"subtitle_14";s:0:"";s:6:"des_14";s:0:"";s:6:"pos_14";s:2:"14";s:11:"subtitle_15";s:0:"";s:6:"des_15";s:0:"";s:6:"pos_15";s:2:"15";}', '', '', 0),
(37, 35, 'a:45:{s:10:"subtitle_1";s:9:"Policy no";s:5:"des_1";s:14:"<p>ECP-409</p>";s:5:"pos_1";s:1:"1";s:10:"subtitle_2";s:7:"Version";s:5:"des_2";s:11:"<p>13.0</p>";s:5:"pos_2";s:1:"2";s:10:"subtitle_3";s:11:"Approved By";s:5:"des_3";s:17:"<p>Prem Anand</p>";s:5:"pos_3";s:1:"3";s:10:"subtitle_4";s:14:"Effective Date";s:5:"des_4";s:23:"<p>January 15, 2014</p>";s:5:"pos_4";s:1:"4";s:10:"subtitle_5";s:7:"Purpose";s:5:"des_5";s:385:"<p>Information systems containing corporate data must possess technical mechanisms and administrative processes that protect the confidentiality, integrity and availability of the software and data they maintain.&nbsp; User authentication techniques and password management policies must be implemented that assure individual accountability for all relevant activity on the system.</p>";s:5:"pos_5";s:1:"5";s:10:"subtitle_6";s:5:"Scope";s:5:"des_6";s:423:"<p>This policy applies to PIPL in its entirety, including all employees, workforce members, physicians and affiliates.&nbsp; In addition, some third parties such as contractors or vendors may be required to abide by parts of this policy if required by PIPL in a Business Associate Contract (BAC).&nbsp; Further, the policy applies to the network, systems and applications that process, store or transmit corporate data.</p>";s:5:"pos_6";s:1:"6";s:10:"subtitle_7";s:6:"Policy";s:5:"des_7";s:1454:"<p>This policy applies to PIPL in its entirety, including all employees, workforce members, physicians and affiliates.&nbsp; In addition, some third parties such as contractors or vendors may be required to abide by parts of this policy if required by PIPL in a Business Associate Contract (BAC).&nbsp; Further, the policy applies to the network, systems and applications that process, store or transmit corporate data.</p><p>Administrators are required to cancel or disable a user&#39;s account upon termination of the users relationship with the organization.</p><p>If a password is suspected to have been compromised, it shall be treated as a security incident and must be reported to the HIPAA Security Officer at <a href="mailto:ephisecurity@aultman.com">HIPAASO@PIPL.com i</a>mmediately.</p><p>1. &nbsp;PIPL will evaluate emerging strong authentication technologies on a periodic basis and implement them when the following criteria is met:</p><ul><li>Technically sound and usable</li><li>Financially reasonable</li><li>Meets business objectives</li></ul><p>2. &nbsp;PIPL will give strong authentication preference to users that pose a higher risk to the organization. &nbsp;High risk users include, but are not limited to:</p><ul><li>Users with Administrator rights to systems that contain corporate data</li><li>Users that connect to the network remotely</li><li>Users that have portable computing devices that may leave the premises</li></ul>";s:5:"pos_7";s:1:"7";s:10:"subtitle_8";s:9:"Retention";s:5:"des_8";s:342:"<p>Every policy and procedure revision/replacement will be maintained for a minimum of six years from the date of its creation or when it was last in effect, whichever is later. Other PIPL requirements may stipulate a longer retention.</p><p>Log-in audit information and logs relevant to security incidents must be retained for six years.</p>";s:5:"pos_8";s:1:"8";s:10:"subtitle_9";s:10:"Compliance";s:5:"des_9";s:276:"<p>Failure to comply with this or any other security policy will result in disciplinary actions as per the Sanction Policy.</p><p>Legal actions also may be taken for violations of applicable regulations and standards such as HIPAA, GLB, Sarbanes-Oxley, PCI DSS and others.</p>";s:5:"pos_9";s:1:"9";s:11:"subtitle_10";s:7:"Form(s)";s:6:"des_10";s:11:"<p>None</p>";s:6:"pos_10";s:2:"10";s:11:"subtitle_11";s:10:"References";s:6:"des_11";s:1781:"<ul><li>Omnibus HIPAA Final Rulemaking, <a href="http://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/administrative/omnibus/index.html">http://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/administrative/omnibus/index.html</a></li><li>International Standards Organization (ISO 27002).</li><li>HIPAA Final Security Rule, 45 CFR Parts 160, 162, and 164, Department of Health and Human Services: &nbsp;http://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/administrative/securityrule/, February 20, 2003.</li><li>American Reinvestment and Recovery Act of 2009 (ARRA)/(HITECH). <a href="http://frwebgate.access.gpo.gov/cgi-bin/getdoc.cgi?dbname=111_cong_bills&amp;docid=f:h1enr.pdf">http://frwebgate.access.gpo.gov/cgi-bin/getdoc.cgi?dbname=111_cong_bills&amp;docid=f:h1enr.pdf.</a></li><li>(The HITECH&nbsp;Act begins at&nbsp;H.R. 1-112 through 1-165 (pp. 112 through 165 in the document).&nbsp;The security and privacy provisions are found at Subtitle D &shy; Privacy, beginning H.R. 1-144 (p. 144)).</li><li>Health Information Privacy, Security, and Your EHR</li><li><a href="http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/ehr-privacy-security">http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/ehr-privacy-security</a></li><li>Achieve Meaningful Use: Protect Electronic Health Information</li><li><a href="http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/achieve-meaningful-use/core-measures/protect-electronic-health-information">http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/achieve-meaningful-use/core-measures/protect-electronic-health-information</a> <a href="http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/achieve-meaningful-use/core-measures-2/protect-electronic-health-information">http://www.healthit.gov/providers-professionals/achieve-meaningful-use/core-measures-2/protect-electronic-health-information</a></li></ul>";s:6:"pos_11";s:2:"11";s:11:"subtitle_12";s:7:"Contact";s:6:"des_12";s:207:"<p>Maria Vasanth Prem Anand, Information Security Officer<br />6, Manakula Vinayagar St<br />Kailash Nagar, ECR. Lawspet, Puducherry 605008<br />India<br />E: prem.anand@pabrai.com<br />P: 1.800.425.9030</p>";s:6:"pos_12";s:2:"12";s:11:"subtitle_13";s:14:"Policy History";s:6:"des_13";s:47:"<p>Initial effective date: January 15, 2014</p>";s:6:"pos_13";s:2:"13";s:11: