(1, '37', 'a:1:{s:6:"client";s:2:"37";}', 'a:2:{s:5:"text1";s:547:"  \r\n<p>raj  data center is part of the hospital facility and is located on the xx floor. There is a badge entry at door to server room.  The vital statistics for the primary data center include: </p>                                                             \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>1672+ sq ft the structure of which is a 1900s, wooden, flat top elementary. Building is approximately 40 years old.</li> \r\n<li>FM200 fire suppression system</li>\r\n<li>Centralized facility monitoring</li>\r\n<li>16 data center internal and perimeter cameras</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n  \r\n";s:5:"text2";s:149:"                                                                \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Access to the data center is through a secured door </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n  \r\n";}', 'a:2:{s:5:"text3";s:167:"  \r\n<p>raj  high voltage utility feeds are provided by  . The data center is supported by one power grid.  A generator is also available. An ATS is in place.</p>\r\n  \r\n";s:5:"text4";s:421:"                                                                \r\n<p>\r\nCat 6 copper with patch panels in each server rack run under the floor. Fiber terminations for fiber based systems also run under the floor.  All low voltage is affixed to ladder racks for any cables exposed above the floor, and cable trays are used under the floor.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>No information was provided on low voltage electrical systems. </p>\r\n  \r\n";}', 'a:3:{s:5:"text5";s:306:"                                                                \r\n<p>\r\nThe CLIENT NAME data center has appropriately sized cooling as reported by the I.T. staff. Back up A/C is available. There are no chillers available. There is one regular 10 ton air handler unit. Redundancy is a 3 ton unit.\r\n</p>\r\n  \r\n";s:5:"text6";s:200:"                                                                \r\n<p>\r\nCLIENT NAME data center is equipped with a regular fire alarm system and one 5 gallon fire extinguisher is available.\r\n</p>\r\n  \r\n";s:5:"text7";s:599:"                                                                \r\n<p>\r\nNo food or beverages were observed in the data center environment, which reduces the risk for accidental spills. Signage is posted that details the fact that food and beverages are not allowed inside the data center.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe building is not located in a potential flood plain. No immediate risks were apparent; however, the ceiling should be inventoried by the facility engineers, and the pipes, if any are present at all, should be inspected to determine the actual amount of risk present to the data center. \r\n</p>\r\n  \r\n";}', 'a:14:{s:5:"text8";s:215:"                                                                \r\n<p><u>Location:</u></p>\r\n<p><u> </u> <u>Size:</u></p>\r\n<p><u>Contents:</u></p>\r\n<p><u>Information:</u></p>\r\n<p>(ex: hours, # staff present)</p>\r\n  \r\n";s:5:"text9";s:169:"                                                                \r\n<p><u>Location:</u></p>\r\n<p><u>Size:</u></p>\r\n<p><u>Contents:</u></p>\r\n<p><u>Information:</u></p>\r\n  \r\n";s:6:"text10";s:4:"  \r\n";s:6:"text11";s:0:"";s:6:"text12";s:4:"  \r\n";s:6:"text13";s:0:"";s:6:"text14";s:4:"  \r\n";s:6:"text15";s:0:"";s:6:"text16";s:4:"  \r\n";s:6:"text17";s:0:"";s:6:"text18";s:4:"  \r\n";s:6:"text19";s:0:"";s:6:"text20";s:4:"  \r\n";s:6:"text21";s:0:"";}', 'a:1:{s:6:"text22";s:1249:"                                                                \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Text of recommendations; select appropriate options, and/or add items specific to the client:</li>\r\n<li>Implement a visitor log and ensure that all visitors/vendors sign in and out. Audit access periodically to identify policy violations.</li>\r\n<li>Restrict key card access to the data center to only those with a job-related need to access equipment therein. The IT Security Team and the Data Center Director (NAME) must approve the final access list.</li>\r\n<li>Consider installing security cameras to record entry and exit to the data center as well as activity within the data center itself.</li>\r\n<li>Lock server racks in all locations, including the data center</li>\r\n<li>Convert the current wet-pipe sprinkler system to a dry-pipe sprinkler system.</li>\r\n<li>Implement a waterless fire suppression system.</li>\r\n<li>Implement a water detection system for the data center.</li>\r\n<li>Assess the sufficiency of its HVAC solution in the data center.</li>\r\n<li>Remove all flammable materials from the data center that are not essential to operations.</li>\r\n<li>Log and secure all equipment (workstations, disk drives, etc.) stored within the data center.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n  \r\n";}', 'a:16:{s:6:"text23";s:1:" ";s:6:"text24";s:1:" ";s:6:"text25";s:1:" ";s:6:"text26";s:1:" ";s:6:"text27";s:1:" ";s:6:"text28";s:1:" ";s:6:"text29";s:1:" ";s:6:"text30";s:1:" ";s:6:"text31";s:1:" ";s:6:"text32";s:1:" ";s:6:"text33";s:1:" ";s:6:"text34";s:1:" ";s:6:"text35";s:1:" ";s:6:"text36";s:1:" ";s:6:"text37";s:1:" ";s:6:"text38";s:1:" ";}', 'a:3:{s:6:"text39";s:1:" ";s:6:"text40";s:1:" ";s:6:"text41";s:1:" ";}', '', 'client_RA_TEMPLATE_Report_09-30-15.doc', 1);
